outputs.output_descr: PEI-Kenya: The project aims to contribute to the realization of the MDGs, Kenya’s Vision 2030 and related Medium Term Plans through enhanced integration of poverty-environment issues in planning, monitoring and investment.
PEI - Mauritania: Country-led poverty-environment mainstreaming programmes, joint UNDP-UNEP regional support programmes, knowledge products and services on environmental mainstreaming.
PEI Botswana aims to support the integration and harmonization of sustainable renewable natural resource management in national, sectoral and district level policy planning and budgetary processes.

PEI - Thailand: The project aims to improve planning and budgeting at national and provincial level for natural resource and ecosystem management for pro-poor growth by addressing gaps and building on potentials at all levels.
Aims to enhance the capacity of government and other stakeholders to integrate environment into sustainable pro-poor development planning and budgeting.

Aims to integrate poverty-environment nexus into national, sub-national, sectoral and UN / UNDP development policy processes and documents - to improve environmental sustainability and ensure pro-poor economic growth.
PEI Uruguay: The intervention’s long term objective is to contribute to the reduction of poverty and vulnerability by mainstreaming the environmental dimension into the planning process.
PEI Nepal: support poverty reduction and inclusive development by integrating climate and environmental concerns and opportunities of the poor into development planning and economic-decision making.

PEI Laos: strengthen capacity of targeted authorities to integrate poverty-envt concerns & opportunities in key devt planning processes to ensure that the country’s rapid economic growth contributes to an equitable devt, sustainable in the long-term.
PEI Liberia: Country-led poverty-environment mainstreaming programmes, joint UNDP-UNEP regional support programmes, knowledge products and services on environmental mainstreaming.
PEI Tanzania: The programme focuses on integrating Environment into the National Strategy of Growth and Reduction of Poverty (NSGRP/MKUKUTA) Implementation
Burkina Faso: Country-led poverty-environment mainstreaming programmes, joint UNDP-UNEP regional support programmes, knowledge products and services on environmental mainstreaming.
Aims to improve selected countries’ capacity to integrate environmental concerns  into policy, planning and implementation processes for poverty reduction and achievement of the MDGs;

PEI Bangladesh: Improving natural resources mgt. and envt outcomes for poor people through mainstreaming pro-poor and gender sensitive envt  & climate change issues into the design & impln of national devt. processes, budgets & economic decision-making.

PEI Mali: Capacity building of national and local actors for the integration of envt into devt policies. Govt structures, local authorities, civil society and the private sector are better informed and aware and able to ensure wise mgt of their envt.

PEI Bhutan -  The main outcome of the project is the improvement of long term capacity of the government to integrate climate change, poverty and environmental concerns in national and subnational  policies, plans and programmes.
